white flash that appears to come out of the pusher plate.<br>
But actually there is a fireball which is going anywhere<br>
from 1000 to 30,000 kilometers per second.<br>
If the pulse unit were detonated at 100 meters from the<br>
plate and its debris was going 1000 km/sec, it will impinge on the plate in just 1 millisecond. The  light of the flash<br>
is going at light speed and is relected by the pusher<br>
plate, within less then a microsecond. To see the <br>
fireball you must use slow motion frame by frame <br>
photography of the pu explosion.<br>
